Tom's dict.cc reader
====================
Look up words in dict.cc dictionaries.

Usage
-----

Install from PyPI. ::

    pip3 install dictcc

Follow these directions to download a dictionary. ::

    python3 -m dictcc download

Run this to confirm that you have saved the dictionary properly. ::

    python3 -m dictcc ls

Then you can look up stuff like this. ::

    python3 -m dictcc lookup elephant

The default is to look for the phrase in all dictionaries.
Restrict to particular languages like this. ::

    python3 -m dictcc lookup -to hr -to sv -from en elephant

Run these to see help. ::

    python3 -m dictcc
    python3 -m dictcc download -help
    python3 -m dictcc ls -help
    python3 -m dictcc lookup -help

Shell integration
-----------------
Consider setting up an alias. Here's one for tcsh. ::

    alias dict.cc python3 -m dictcc lookup

Here's one for sh. ::

    alias dict.cc='python3 -m dictcc lookup'

Implementation
--------------
This is a Python module.
Source code is at https://thomaslevine.com/scm/dict.cc/.
The command line interface uses `horetu <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/horetu/>`_.

History
-------
The idea of underlining the search term comes from
Matthias Bloch's `woerterbuch.pl <https://www1.dict.cc/download/woerterbuch.pl>`_.
